{
  "texts": [
    "On the prediction axis, the 'background' tag assists in quantifying the percentage of nuclei that were not detected.",
    "Meanwhile, the GT axis helps us determine whether background elements are incorrectly classified as nuclei.",
    "By extracting values from these matrices, we calculate the balanced accuracy for each class, considering or disregarding the background label.",
    "This information is presented in Figs.",
    "10 and 11, respectively."
  ]
}